Beijing faced a water crisis with more residents than available supply.
China aims to reduce water consumption by 20% by 2010 to prevent shortages.
The government plans to implement consumption quotas and hold officials accountable for water management.
Despite increased grain production, China still anticipates a significant shortage.
Water scarcity poses a threat to agriculture, wildlife, and energy production.
The Three Gorges Dam opened floodgates to alleviate water shortages along the Yangtze River.
Severe droughts have impacted water levels, prompting conservation efforts and desalination projects in affected regions like Shandong Province.
